main event: No visual sighting of an unidentified object was reported. The incident consisted of a report of an unidentified aircraft heard on radio frequencies, but no aircraft was identified in the Cartwright, Labrador area.
interesting points: The initial report was of an unidentified aircraft heard on 13,240 kilocycles, south-bound over Labrador at 0530Z on March 7, 1951.
The sighting was reported by Carnage ATC, Eastern Airways, and Aeropost Naval Radio, but no aircraft flight plan or position report could be found to indicate an aircraft in the Cartwright area.
NEAC (Newfoundland) noted that sonic disturbances in this area are usually caused by transient aircraft, and additional information would be provided upon receipt.
A later message indicates a check of all bases and aircraft control centers within the NEAC area revealed no aircraft over the Cartwright, Labrador area on March 23, 1951.
The unidentified aircraft was still classified as unidentified within the Goose area.
sighted object: no visual sighting of an unidentified object
witnesses: Carnage ATC, Eastern Airways, Aeropost Naval Radio
